    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Gábor Perényi (Augsburg, 16 July 1550)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He is attaching the letter he recently received from the
                            royal legate in Constantinople about Gábor Perényi’s brother. He would
                            prefer to be in Eger if the King permitted it, but since he is here, he
                            recommends himself and his services to Perényi. It is very useful for
                            young noblemen to stay at the royal court because they can learn a lot
                            there, so he also recommends him to follow the King’s court, where he
                            can entertain himself in the company of other young noblemen.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Spectabilis et Magnifice Domine et Amice nobis Honorandissime,
                    salutem et nostri commendationem! </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quae nova ex parte <persName>fratris</persName><note xml:id="note.1"
                        >Ferenc Perényi was captured and kept hostage from 1532, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kasza</hi> 2021, 60.</note> Dominationis Vestrae
                    Magnificae ex <placeName>Constantinopoli</placeName> ab oratore maiestatis
                    regiae habeamus, eorum litteras in specie praesentibus inclusas ad eandem <add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="insert">pro</add> tuendis rebus suis mittimus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Nos, si per voluntatem <persName>maiestatis regiae</persName>
                    licuisset, hoc tempore libentius <placeName>Agriae</placeName><note
                        xml:id="note.2">Eger.</note> essemus, quam hic, ubi caritas omnium rerum
                    magna est, verum ea nostra voluntas adempta nobis est, domestica igitur nostra
                    negotia Dominationi Vestrae Magnificae commendamus rogamusque, ut paratam
                    vicinitatem nobiscum habeat. Nobilibus iuvenibus aula principum quantae
                    utilitati sit, res ipsa loquitur, in ea enim ad bonos mores retinendos,
                    cognitionemque plurimarum rerum, utilia ab ingenuis imbibuntur, domi educati,
                    cum nihil, nisi domestica videant, audiant, experianturque, ultra haec sapere
                    non possunt, quam utilissimum foret, si Dominatio Vestra Magnifica aulam
                    principis ad aliquod tempus sequeretur. Sunt hic alii etiam proceres iuvenes
                    regni Hungariae, quibus quandoque taedium, si quid forte conciperet, excutere
                    possit; illis, ut nos videmus, aulica conversatio in multis utilis <milestone
                        unit="pb"/>est. In reliquo Dominationem Vestram Magnificam optamus valere
                    feliciter.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Augustae</placeName> 16. Iulii anno Domini 1550.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Agriensis etc. manu propria</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
